Sentencas: Novel three-layered intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrolytes based on gadolinium doped ceria (GDC) are developed to suppress the electronic conductivity of GDC, to improve the mechanical properties of the cell and to minimize power loss due to mixed conductive nature of GDC.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three different electrolytes are fabricated by sandwiching thin YSZ.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: ScSZ and ScCeSZ between two relatively thick GDC layers.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An electrolyte composed of pure GDC is also manufactured for comparison.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: NiO/GDC and LSCF/GDC electrodes are then coated on the electrolytes by a screen printing route.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SEM results show that it is possible to obtain dense and crack free thin layers of YSZ, ScSZ and ScCeSZ between two GDC layers without delamination.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Performance measurements indicate that interlayered thin electrolytes act as an electronic conduction barrier and improve open circuit voltages (OCVs) of GDC based cells.
Titulo: Novel structured gadolinium doped ceria based electrolytes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
